      • next

        ConcurrentIteratorItem<T> next()
                        throws java.util.NoSuchElementException
        Get the next element after registering a IConcurrentIterator.StateListener and receiving HAS_NEXT. If the list is of finite length, the listener notification of transition to state FINISHED will occur after the last value has been fetched. Since this transition may involve multiple threads, a race condition may result in NoSuchElementException which can be treated as equivalent to SLEEP which signals that the listener should pause reading items until it receives the next state change notification.
        Returns:
        Throws:
        {@link - java.util.NoSuchElementException} if state is anything other than HAS_NEXT.
        java.util.NoSuchElementException
